IP Address: This is the logical unique identifier for a certain network/device on a network.

There are 2 main types of IP Addresses:

-IPv4: A 32-bit string of numbers with 4 sets of octets. This is the old standard for IP addresses as we have literally run out of available IPs on this standard due to poor
management and unpredictability of the internet becoming as big as it did. A big issue with the distribution of these IPs was the use of classes.
